\r\ndom &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \nCc: &quot;vedic-astrology@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;=\r\nvedic-astrology@yahoogroups.com&gt;; &quot;JyotishGroup@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;JyotishGr=\r\noup@yahoogroups.com&gt;; &quot;JyotishWritings@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;JyotishWritings@ya=\r\nhoogroups.com&gt; \nSent: Tuesday, 5 March 2013 10:03 AM\nSubject: [JyotishWriti=\r\nngs] Re: Karma, Phala, Remedies, Blessings, Curses etc (Re: few questions)\n=\r\n \n\n=C2=A0 \nNamaste,\n=C2=A0\nSome quick miscellaneous replies to a few select=\r\ned questions/comments that came in response to my writeup yesterday.\n=C2=A0=\r\n\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nComment 1: &quot;If the remedial measures can only push=\r\n the karma phala down to manifest \nat a later date/birth then isn&#39;t it a fu=\r\ntile=C2=A0exercise. Why not accept \nwhatever comes our way as &#39;PRASAD&#39; from=\r\n Isvara and move on.&quot;\n=C2=A0\nMy response: The final goal is indeed to reach=\r\n a state of mind where one can accept the fruits of all karmas as prasad of=\r\n Lord, with an equanimous mind. However, it is not easy. When we receive th=\r\ne fruits of some really terrible karmas, our mind gets so twisted and agita=\r\nted that we lose our balance and our judgment gets badly beated. This may r=\r\nesult in further bad karmas being committed in that agitated/confused state=\r\n.\n=C2=A0\nThus, it IS sometimes useful to push off some really bad impending=\r\n karmas when one is still in a position to do so. If one reaches a calmer s=\r\ntate of mind in that borrowed time, one may be able to handle the bad fruit=\r\ns better. It is even possible theoretically that one pushes off a really ba=\r\nd karma, makes progress during that borrowed\n time, reaches an equanimous s=\r\ntate of mind, becomes liberated and then faces the karma as a liberated bei=\r\nng with a totally equanimous mind that does not get agitated.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nComment 2: Prarabda karma is which was already done and =\r\nsanchitha and agami are what we going to do.\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: Actually s=\r\nanchita karmas are also karmas already done. Sanchita means &quot;piled up&quot;. Pra=\r\nrabdha karmas are different in the sense that their fructification has alre=\r\nady begun. The verb &quot;prArabh&quot; means &quot;to begin&quot;. Its noun form &quot;prArambha&quot; m=\r\neans &quot;beginning&quot; and its gerund noun form &quot;prArabdha&quot; means &quot;the [one that =\r\nwas] begun&quot;. Prarabdha karmas are actions for which the process of reaction=\r\n has already begun and in the pipeline. Whereas sanchita karmas are piled u=\r\np karmas that have not kicked off their fruits yet. They can be delayed ind=\r\nefinitely. If one becomes liberated while living, one can merge in Cosmic S=\r\nelf without experiencing the fruits of sanchita karmas. However, fruits of =\r\nprarabdha karmas are already in the pipeline and need to be experienced eve=\r\nn by a liberated being.\n=C2=A0\nThough fruits of prarabdha karmas are alread=\r\ny in the pipeline, even they can actually be delayed or manipulated. Bottom=\r\nline is that there are agents of delivery at the physical and subtle level =\r\neven for things deep in the pipeline and hence some limited adjustment is p=\r\nossible.\n\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nComment 3:How does nishkam karma wo=\r\nrks? In other words, when a doer detaches himself from an action, where doe=\r\ns the reaction goes?\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: If one identifies with a body-mind=\r\n complex and a limited sense of self-identification and pursues its selfish=\r\n agenda, one keeps accumulating karmas. But, if one has minimal identificat=\r\nion with a body-mind complex to just sustain it, pursues no agenda and enga=\r\nges in whatever action is natural in the situation one is in (but not drive=\r\nn by any conditioning, i.e. agendas or desires or likes/dislikes), then one=\r\n is untouched by karmas performed in that state.\n=C2=A0\nIn the words of Swa=\r\nmi Sivananda of Hrishikesh, &quot;The accumulated and current actions of a Jnani=\r\n take shelter in Brahmanda Prakriti&quot;. In other words, Sanchita karmas (pile=\r\nd up actions from past that have not yet begun fructifying) and aagami karm=\r\nas (actions being performed right now) of a liberated being take shelted in=\r\n\n Cosmic Kinetic Consciousness (Brahmanda Prakriti).\n\n=C2=A0*=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 =\r\n*\n=C2=A0\nComment 4: If my destiny is to suffer, why should I pray to God? A=\r\nnd if i am being \npunished for some kind of bad karma from the past, why am=\r\n i not aware of it? It is like getting punishment without knowing your bad =\r\ndeeds.\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: One need not pray to God.All one needs to do is =\r\nto stop engaging in problematic karmas to add to the pile of such karmas fr=\r\nom the past. More importantly, one needs to reach a calm and sustainable st=\r\nate of mind in which that can be maintained even in the middle of a tumulto=\r\nus hurricane caused in one&#39;s life due to serious bad karmas from the past. =\r\nOnce serious troubles set in or mind focuses on sense objects, material wor=\r\nld and one&#39;s pleasures and pains, mind tends to lose its balance and judgme=\r\nnt, starts pursuing its limited selfish agendas and starts performing even =\r\nmore bad karmas. Thus, praying to God and contemplating various ideals and =\r\nqualities that God represents can give a shelter to the mind in which it ca=\r\nn maintain some calmness, balance and judgment. If that is not the case for=\r\n one, perhaps one needs to perfect it further.\n=C2=A0\nGod has no agenda to =\r\neither punish you or hide the reason. God is an impartial balancer of react=\r\nions to all actions. If there is something unreasonable about the reaction =\r\nyou are getting, it means your action had a similar unreasonableness.\n\n=C2=\r\n=A0Let me turn around your question on being &quot;aware&quot; and ask a simple quest=\r\nion. When we cause loss or hurt to someone, do we always tell that person w=\r\nhy we are doing it? If not, how can we expect someone to tell us before cau=\r\nsing loss or hurt to us? If I caused terrible strife to someone pious and p=\r\nure for no reason, then Nature will use someone in future to cause terrible=\r\n strife to me despite my piety and purity and apparently for no reason.\n=C2=\r\n=A0\nIn fact, what will you achieve by knowing exactly what was the action t=\r\nhat caused what is happening to you right now? Why is that useful? More use=\r\nful is your conscience (a representation of God in each heart) that tells y=\r\nou right from wrong. It constantly gives guidance on which actions will giv=\r\ne good reactions *in future*.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nComment 5: Vasa=\r\nna can be for wealth, fame, power, domination (a struggle for power!) etc. =\r\nMany ripus, many reasons...!\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: Well-said. Though we are d=\r\niscussing karma and karma phala here, the root cause of karma is vasana in =\r\nchittaakasha. (Chidaakaasha is the space of pure consciousness and chittaak=\r\naasha is the space of conditioned consciousness that has likes, dislikes, d=\r\nesires, agendas etc.) Vasishtha defined liberation as overcoming vasanas in=\r\n Yoga Vaasishtham and Patanjali defined yoga as &quot;chitta vR^itti nirodhaH yo=\r\ngaH&quot; (resisting the working of conditioning is oneness with Cosmic Self) in=\r\n Yoga Sutras. Until we overcome our vasanas, we are bound. Some are dense a=\r\nnd some are very subtle. But all of them bind us.\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=\r\n=C2=A0\nComment 6:1. As per Shri Vimalananda, you may also offer all the kar=\r\nmas as Homa to inner \ndevas or ishta devta? He mentioned that there is less=\r\ner of suffering if \nyou do that. Who gets the remaining delta suffering?\n=\r\n=C2=A0\nMy Response: Karmaphala for a specific karma is not a function of th=\r\nat karma alone. It is a function of that karma and one&#39;s current state of m=\r\nind. If someone serves spoiled food, one may get an upset stomach for half =\r\nday or diaria for a week. It depends on how strong one is. Similarly, the s=\r\name karmaphala set in motion by the same external agents of delivery (physi=\r\ncal & subtle) can cause different reaction inside one, depending on one&#39;s c=\r\nurrent state of mind.\n=C2=A0\nAn idle mind is devil&#39;s workshop. Our minds ke=\r\nep vibrating with various notions and thoughts. A mind vibrating with selfi=\r\nsh desires and unnecessary clutter/confusion *amplifies* the negative effec=\r\nts of one&#39;s environment (through which fruits of karmas are\n administered).=\r\n\n=C2=A0\nIf one thinks of ishta devata with reverence and contemplates vario=\r\nus ideals and qualities of ishta devata and mind vibrates with saattwik ene=\r\nrgy, it absorbs the negative effects of one&#39;s environment better or at leas=\r\nt does not amplify them.\n=C2=A0\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n--------\nAstrology =\r\n& Spirituality Resources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n--------\n\n=C2=A0\n\n=\r\n\n&gt;________________________________\n&gt; From: Narasimha P.V.R. Rao &lt;pvr108@yah=\r\noo.com&gt;\n&gt;To: Vedic Wisdom &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \n&gt;Sent: Sunday, Ma=\r\nrch 3, 2013 5:26 PM\n&gt;Subject: Karma, Phala, Remedies, Blessings, Curses etc=\r\n (Re: few questions)\n&gt; \n&gt;\n&gt;Namaste friends,\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Ajit&#39;s reply to Digamb=\r\ner ji&#39;s nice questions is thoughtful. I will add my 2 cents.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=\r\n=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=C2=A0The cosmos run=\r\ns based on the fundamental law that each action (karma) gives a reaction/re=\r\nsult (karmaphala) commensurate with it. Shakti is the sum total of all the =\r\nbeings with various agendas engaging in various karmas and experiencing var=\r\nious karmaphalas. Purusha is the witness of it all.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;Though each ka=\r\nrma should give karmaphala that is commensurate with it, that requires an *=\r\nagent* to deliver the karmaphala, i.e. another being. So this requires a co=\r\nmplicated balancing act on part of Cosmic Cumulative Kinetic Consciousness =\r\n(i.e. Shakti). There are very complicated rules that decide the *sequencing=\r\n* of karmaphalas and picking of agents for their delivery.\n&gt;\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;At an=\r\ny time, some karmas from one&#39;s past are placed in a &quot;must experience karmap=\r\nhala in this life&quot; pool, some karmas in a &quot;preferably experience karmaphala=\r\n in this life&quot; pool and the rest in the third pool which may not be experie=\r\nnced anytime soon. The way karmas are assigned and ordered in these pools i=\r\ns based on the balancing of karma/karmaphala sequencing of all beings.\n&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0\n&gt;The assignment and ordering of these pools will constantly undergo chu=\r\nrn as one engages in various new actions and adds them to the pools. Also, =\r\nas new people enter one&#39;s life, possibilities in terms of karmaphala delive=\r\nry agents and sequencing may change and hence the pools may be re-arranged.=\r\n\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;As one engages in remedial measures suc=\r\nh as prayers, fasting, donations etc, one may transform one&#39;s nature, chang=\r\ne one&#39;s vulnerabilities or re-arrange one&#39;s dynamics with other beings (inc=\r\nluding planets, deities etc, who are the subtle agents of delivery of karma=\r\nphala, who operate through other people who act as physical agents of deliv=\r\nery!). The karma pools may be re-arranged as a result. Some undesirable kar=\r\nmas may be downgraded to a lower pool or pushed down in order within the sa=\r\nme pool. Or, some desirable karmas may be upgraded to a higher pool or push=\r\ned up in order within the same pool.\n&gt;=C2=A0When someone curses or blesses =\r\none, with sufficient mental force behind it (this is the key), the same thi=\r\nng can happen. It is all about re-arranging karmas between the karmik pools=\r\n. Every action by one, or even people around one, has the potential to re-a=\r\nrrange one&#39;s karmik pools. A karma about to give karmaphala may be postpone=\r\nd or a karma that was not to give karmaphala anytime soon may be advanced s=\r\nooner.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;However, remember that the remedial measure has to be as in=\r\ntense as the karma that it is trying to manipulate. You can move a small ro=\r\nck with small force, but you need a large force to move a big rock or a hil=\r\nl.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;\n&gt;If there is no negative karma in one&#39;s pool that can give a s=\r\npecific result, nobody can make one experience that result, no matter what =\r\nritual one does. However, even great souls have a lot of negative karmas in=\r\n their optional pool and even evil people have a lot of positive karmas in =\r\ntheir optional pool, and hence powerful remedies, curses and blessings can =\r\noften make some difference.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;This point is well illustrated by the =\r\n&quot;Guru Charitra&quot; story Digamber ji referred in his point (3).\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;*=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;If one thinks that one can escape the fruits of one&#39;s =\r\nactions, one is mistakened. God is not like us human beings, who may show f=\r\navoritism towards those who praise them or bribe them. The He-aspect of God=\r\n is a witness to the play of actions and fruits. The She-aspect of God is t=\r\nhe power that impartially and impassionately manages the fine balance and o=\r\nrder within this play of actions and fruits. All beings are equal in Her ey=\r\nes, from the lowest of evil persons to the noblest of saints. She administe=\r\nrs just and balanced delivery of fruits to actions using available agents.\n=\r\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;The karmas we committed in the past are already in the pipeline an=\r\nd will give their results sooner or later. The best we can do with them, wi=\r\nth some effort, is to perhaps reorder them somewhat. The most important thi=\r\nng is to not add more serious bad karmas to the pipeline now. Simply put, s=\r\nelfish actions and actions that cause pain or harm to others are bad karmas=\r\n and selfless actions and actions that cause pleasure or benefit to others =\r\nare good karmas.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;When it comes to manipulating the pre-existing pi=\r\npeline of karmas awaiting karmaphala, through conscious effort and current =\r\naction, yes, it is possible and general guidelines are available in shastra=\r\ns, but we can&#39;t be certain about the specific impact of each action. One th=\r\ning is for sure - remedial measure for overcoming a karma has to be commens=\r\nurate with the karma\n itself.\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;You need only small force to push a =\r\ncat out of your way, but need a large force to push an elephant.\n&gt;\n&gt;=C2=A0\n=\r\n&gt;Best regards,\n&gt;Narasimha\n&gt;--------\n&gt;Astrology & Spirituality Resources: ht=\r\ntp://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n&gt;--------\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;\n&gt;&gt;________________________=\r\n________\n&gt;&gt; From: Ajit Krishnan &lt;ajit.krishnan@...&gt;\n&gt;&gt;To: vedic-wisdo=\r\nm@yahoogroups.com \n&gt;&gt;Sent: Tuesday, February 26, 2013 11:29 PM\n&gt;&gt;Subject: R=\r\ne: [vedic-wisdom] few questions\n&gt;&gt; \n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0 \n&gt;&gt;Dear=C2=A0Digamber,\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n&gt;\n&gt;&gt;When a kingdom had no royal heirs, a special elephant was appointed by =\r\nthe courtiers to randomly pick the next king. Thus, it was possible for a b=\r\neggar to suddenly find himself the king. Whose karma is this?=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n&gt;Vasishtha gives two answers: (1) This is the karma of the ministers, king,=\r\n and all the citizens, and (2) This is the karma of the beggar turned king.=\r\n\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Everything is interrelated. The beggar&#39;s karma made him a king. Th=\r\ne elephant&#39;s karma allowed him to be the one chosen to pick the king. The m=\r\ninister&#39;s karma allowed them to appoint the elephant to pick the king. And =\r\nthe citizens&#39; karma allowed them to live in such a kingdom, and accept the =\r\nresult.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;The sanskrit word &quot;shaapa&quot; means a curse, or promise, or oa=\r\nth. Many of the curses that we see are for the benefit of mankind, and are =\r\nactually blessings. At the end of the day, some people with a certain amoun=\r\nt of purity of speech discharge their tapas shakti through speech.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;=\r\nWhen it comes to people and their karmic pipeline, we usually make an assum=\r\nption. We assume that there is a person, and separate from the person are h=\r\nis many karmas. These karmas can &#39;come&#39; to the person from time to time. We=\r\n then want someone to come and remove all the &quot;bad&quot; karmas from our karmic =\r\npipeline.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Vasishtha teaches us that a &#39;person&#39; and &#39;karma&#39; are the =\r\nsame thing. You are your karmas. And you are nothing but your mind-impressi=\r\nons ... your vaasanaas. In other words, your vaasanaas are your karmas.\n&gt;&gt;\n=\r\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;If you can change your vaasanaas, you have changed your karma. Or cour=\r\nse, that is easier said than done.\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Any moment when your mind become=\r\ns quiet is a blessing. Any moment when your mind becomes agitated is a curs=\r\ne. As sadhakas, we run after quieting the mind !\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;sasneham,\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0=\r\n\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0 =C2=A0ajit\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;On Tue, Feb 26, 2013 at 8:08 AM, &lt;dgporob@yahoo.c=\r\nom&gt; wrote:\n&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;Dear Narasimha Ji,\n&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 =C2=A0 I was pon=\r\ndering over few things we routinely come across as a part of worship and ho=\r\nw it manipulates karma pipe line,\n&gt;&gt;&gt;(1) When someone gives a `curse&#39; or do=\r\nes a prayoga such as `maran&#39; or `uchhatan&#39; what happens to a person who is =\r\nat receiving end, does his bad karma comes forward or is it a new parabdha =\r\nthat is created. I vaguely remember Vimalananda mentioning something about =\r\na Saint&#39;s curse in Aghora trilogy.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;(2) On similar note, what happens whe=\r\nn you get `blessings&#39; say from a saint or elders? We also come across lot o=\r\nf tantric items like Rudraksha, Parad Shivalinga or say Shwetarka Ganapati =\r\n=E2=80=93 what do this items really do if they work? Something similar with=\r\n wearing gemstones for planets =E2=80=93 do they bring forward good karmas =\r\nor they create new ones?\n&gt;&gt;&gt;(3) I recollect an episode from famous &quot;Gurucha=\r\nritra&quot; (well known in Maharashtra), wherein a just widowed lady cried out t=\r\no Shri Guru &quot;If we cannot change `parabdha, then, why do we worship God at =\r\nall&quot;. At that point Shri Guru rejuvenates her dead husband, but later tells=\r\n his shisya, that he has only readjusted the karma from next birth. [Please=\r\n excuse me if this is not exact word to word, as I am trying to recollect t=\r\nhis episode from old memory]. So question I have is, does our sadhana chang=\r\ne karmaphal to a great extent or it is just our perception that changes?\n&gt;&gt;=\r\n&gt;Thanking you,\n&gt;&gt;&gt;Digamber\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n\n\n \r\n---657894450-971298693-1362462344=:44622\r\nConten