riencing various karmaphal=\r\nas. Purusha is the witness of it all.&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Though each karm=\r\na should give karmaphala that is commensurate with it, that requires an *ag=\r\nent* to deliver the\n karmaphala, i.e. another\n being. So this\n requires a c=\r\nomplicated balancing act on part of Cosmic Cumulative Kinetic Consciousness=\r\n (i.e. Shakti). There are very complicated rules that decide the *sequencin=\r\ng* of karmaphalas and picking of agents for their delivery.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&=\r\nnbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;At any time, some karmas from one&#39;s past are placed in a &quot;&lt;=\r\nspan style=3D&quot;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;must &lt;/span&gt;experience karmaphala in this=\r\n life&quot; pool, some karmas in a &quot;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;preferabl=\r\ny &lt;/span&gt;experience karmaphala in this life&quot; pool and the rest in the third=\r\n pool which may not be experienced anytime soon. The way karmas are assigne=\r\nd and ordered in these pools is based on the balancing of karma/karmaphala =\r\nsequencing of all beings.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The assignment and ord=\r\nering of these pools will constantly undergo churn as one engages in variou=\r\ns new actions and adds them to the pools. Also, as new people enter one&#39;s l=\r\nife, possibilities in terms of karmaphala delivery agents\n and sequencing m=\r\nay change and hence the pools may be re-arranged.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;di=\r\nv&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=\r\np;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;As one engages in remedial meas=\r\nures such as prayers, fasting, donations etc, one may transform one&#39;s natur=\r\ne, change one&#39;s vulnerabilities or re-arrange one&#39;s dynamics with other bei=\r\nngs (including planets, deities etc, who are the subtle agents of delivery =\r\nof karmaphala, who operate through other people who act as physical agents =\r\nof delivery!). The karma pools may be re-arranged as a result. Some undesir=\r\nable karmas may be downgraded to a lower pool or pushed down in order withi=\r\nn the same pool. Or, some desirable karmas may be upgraded to a higher pool=\r\n or pushed up in order within the same pool.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;When som=\r\neone curses or blesses one, with &lt;span style=3D&quot;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;suffici=\r\nent &lt;/span&gt;mental force behind it (this is the key),\n the same thing &lt;span&gt;=\r\ncan &lt;/span&gt;happen. It is all about re-arranging karmas between the karmik p=\r\nools. Every action by one, or even people around one, has the &lt;span style=\r\n=3D&quot;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;potential &lt;/span&gt;to re-arrange one&#39;s karmik pools. =\r\nA karma about to give karmaphala may be postponed or a karma that was not t=\r\no give karmaphala anytime soon may be advanced sooner.&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div=\r\n&gt;However, remember that the remedial measure has to be as intense as the ka=\r\nrma that it is trying to manipulate. You can move a small rock with small f=\r\norce, but you need a large force to move a big rock or a hill.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&nb=\r\nsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;If there is no negative karma in one&#39;s pool that can give a &lt;sp=\r\nan style=3D&quot;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;specific &lt;/span&gt;result, nobody can make one=\r\n experience &lt;span style=3D&quot;font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;that &lt;/span&gt;result, no matte=\r\nr what ritual one does. However, even great souls have a lot of negative ka=\r\nrmas in their optional pool and even evil people\n have a lot of positive ka=\r\nrmas in their optional pool, and hence powerful remedies, curses and blessi=\r\nngs can often make some difference.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This point i=\r\ns well illustrated by the &quot;Guru Charitra&quot; story Digamber ji referred in his=\r\n point (3).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div=\r\n&gt;&lt;div&gt;If one thinks that one can escape the fruits of one&#39;s actions, one is=\r\n mistakened. God is not like us human beings, who may show favoritism towar=\r\nds those who praise them or bribe them. The He-aspect of God is a witness t=\r\no the play of actions and fruits. The She-aspect of God is the power that i=\r\nmpartially and impassionately manages the fine balance and order within thi=\r\ns play of actions and fruits. All beings are equal in Her eyes, from the lo=\r\nwest of evil persons to the noblest of saints. She administers just and bal=\r\nanced delivery of fruits to actions using\n available agents.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbs=\r\np;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;The karmas we committed in the past are already in the pipeline=\r\n and will give their results sooner or later. The best we can do with them,=\r\n with some effort, is to perhaps reorder them somewhat. The most important =\r\nthing is to not add more serious bad karmas to the pipeline &lt;span style=3D&quot;=\r\nfont-style:italic;&quot;&gt;n&lt;span&gt;ow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; Simply put, selfi=\r\nsh actions and actions that cause pain or harm to others are bad karmas and=\r\n selfless actions and actions that cause pleasure or benefit to others are =\r\ngood karmas.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;When it comes to manipulating the pre-existing pi=\r\npeline of karmas awaiting karmaphala, through conscious effort and current =\r\naction, yes, it is possible and general guidelines are available in shastra=\r\ns, but we can&#39;t be certain about the specific impact of each action. One th=\r\ning is for sure - remedial measure for overcoming a karma has to be commens=\r\nurate with the karma\n itself.&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;You need only small force to pus=\r\nh a cat out of your way, but need a large force to push an elephant.&lt;br&gt;&lt;di=\r\nv style=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 13px; background-color: transpar=\r\nent; font-style: normal; font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; =\r\n&quot;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Best regards,&lt;br&gt;Narasimha&lt;br&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;Astrology &amp; Spiri=\r\ntuality Resources: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;http://www=\r\n.vedicastrologer.org/&quot;&gt;http://www.VedicAstrologer.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=\r\n=3D&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 13px; background-color: transparent; fo=\r\nnt-style: normal; font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; &quot;&gt;-----=\r\n---&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;blockquote style=3D&quot;border-left:2px solid rgb(16, =\r\n16, 255);&quot;&gt;  &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, =\r\nsans-serif; &quot;&gt; &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: &#39;times new roman=\r\n&#39;, &#39;new york&#39;, times, serif; &quot;&gt; &lt;div dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; &lt;font face=3D&quot;Arial&quot; size=\r\n=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;\n &lt;hr size=3D&quot;1&quot;&gt;  &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/span&gt;=\r\n&lt;/b&gt; Ajit Krishnan &lt;ajit.krishnan@...&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;fo=\r\nnt-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;To:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com &lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span =\r\nstyle=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Sent:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Tuesday, February 26, 2013 11:=\r\n29 PM&lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;Subject:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Re: [ved=\r\nic-wisdom] few questions&lt;br&gt; &lt;/font&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;div id=3D&quot;yiv2116634567&quot;&gt;\n=\r\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;span&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;\n\n\n\n    &lt;div id=3D&quot;yiv2116634567ygrp-=\r\ntext&quot;&gt;\n      \n      \n      &lt;div&gt;Dear&nbsp;Digamber,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;di=\r\nv&gt;When a kingdom had no royal heirs, a special elephant was appointed by th=\r\ne courtiers to randomly pick the next king. Thus, it was possible for a beg=\r\ngar to suddenly find himself the king. Whose karma is this?&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;d=\r\niv&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Vasishtha gives two answers: (1) This is the karma of the=\r\n ministers, king, and all the citizens, and (2) This is the karma of the be=\r\nggar turned king.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Everything is interrelated. The =\r\nbeggar&#39;s karma made him a king. The elephant&#39;s karma allowed him to be the =\r\none chosen to pick the king. The minister&#39;s karma allowed them to appoint t=\r\nhe elephant to pick the king. And the citizens&#39; karma allowed them to live =\r\nin such a kingdom, and accept the result.&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;The sa=\r\nnskrit word &quot;shaapa&quot; means a curse, or promise, or oath. Many of the curses=\r\n that we see are for the benefit of mankind, and are actually blessings. At=\r\n the end of the day, some people with a certain amount of purity of speech =\r\ndischarge their tapas shakti through speech.&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Whe=\r\nn it comes to people and their karmic pipeline, we usually make an assumpti=\r\non. We assume that there is a person, and separate from the person are his =\r\nmany karmas. These karmas can &#39;come&#39; to the person from time to time. We th=\r\nen want someone to come and remove all the &quot;bad&quot; karmas from our karmic pip=\r\neline.&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Vasishtha teaches us that a &#39;person&#39; and =\r\n&#39;karma&#39; are the same thing. You are your karmas. And you are nothing but yo=\r\nur mind-impressions ... your vaasanaas. In other words, your vaasanaas are =\r\nyour karmas.&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;If you can change your vaasanaas, y=\r\nou have changed your karma. Or course, that is easier said than done.&lt;/div&gt;=\r\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Any moment when your mind becomes quiet is a blessing. =\r\nAny moment when your mind becomes agitated is a curse. As sadhakas, we run =\r\nafter quieting the mind !&lt;/div&gt;\n\n&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;sasneham,&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;d=\r\niv&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&nbsp; &nbsp;ajit&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;div class=3D&quot;yi=\r\nv2116634567gmail_quote&quot;&gt;On Tue, Feb 26, 2013 at 8:08 AM,  &lt;span dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;=\r\n&gt;&lt;&lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:dgporob@...&quot; target=3D&quot;_bl=\r\nank&quot; href=3D&quot;mailto:dgporob@...&quot;&gt;dgporob@...&lt;/a&gt;&gt;&lt;/span&gt; wro=\r\nte:&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote class=3D&quot;yiv2116634567gmail_quote&quot; style=3D&quot;border-left:=\r\n1px #ccc solid;&quot;&gt;\n\nDear Narasimha Ji,&lt;br&gt;\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; I was=\r\n pondering over few things we routinely come across as a part of worship an=\r\nd how it manipulates karma pipe line,&lt;br&gt;\n(1) When someone gives a `curse&#39; =\r\nor does a prayoga such as `maran&#39; or `uchhatan&#39; what happens to a person wh=\r\no is at receiving end, does his bad karma comes forward or is it a new para=\r\nbdha that is created. I vaguely remember Vimalananda mentioning something a=\r\nbout a Saint&#39;s curse in Aghora trilogy.&lt;br&gt;\n\n\n(2) On similar note, what hap=\r\npens when you get `blessings&#39; say from a saint or elders? We also come acro=\r\nss lot of tantric items like Rudraksha, Parad Shivalinga or say Shwetarka G=\r\nanapati =E2=80=93 what do this items really do if they work? Something simi=\r\nlar with wearing gemstones for planets =E2